## 2. Empirical Evidence Supporting Abortion Legality

### 2.1. Impact on Women's Health: The Mexico Case Study

A landmark study analyzing abortion law reforms in Mexico provides compelling evidence of the health benefits of legal abortion ([Clarke & Mühlrad, 2021](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jhealeco.2020.102413)).

| Outcome                          | Effect of Legal Abortion Reform in Mexico DF | Interpretation                         |
|---------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| Abortion-related morbidity       | Decreased by ~20%                           | Fewer complications from unsafe abortion |
| Hemorrhage in early pregnancy    | Decreased by ~35%                           | Reduced severe pregnancy complications |
| Maternal mortality               | Decreased (less precise estimates)         | Trend towards fewer deaths            |
| Birth rates                     | Reduced by ~8%                             | Fewer unwanted pregnancies carried to term |

- **Key Insight**: Legalizing abortion in Mexico City sharply reduced hospitalizations for abortion-related complications and early pregnancy hemorrhages, indicating safer reproductive health outcomes.

- **No Significant Effect of Restrictive Laws**: Subsequent regressive abortion laws in other Mexican states showed little impact on morbidity or mortality, suggesting that de jure restrictions may not translate into effective barriers or health outcomes ([Clarke & Mühlrad, 2021](https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jhealeco.2020.102413)).

### 2.2. Historical Data from the United States

Before Roe v. Wade (1973), illegal abortions were common and dangerous, causing thousands of deaths annually. After legalization:

- Abortion-related deaths dropped from approximately 90 in 1972 to 16 in 1980.

- Legal abortion is significantly safer than childbirth, with mortality rates about seven times lower ([Tyrer, 1992](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12340404/)).

### 2.3. Societal and Economic Impacts

- Legal abortion contributes to women's empowerment by allowing them to plan education, careers, and family life.

- It reduces the incidence of unwanted births, which are correlated with higher rates of poverty, child abuse, and social problems ([Pollitt, 2019](https://www.newyorker.com/news/daily-comment/how-the-right-to-legal-abortion-changed-the-arc-of-all-womens-lives)).

